# nano-ros direnv config.
#
# Phase 218.C — single source of truth for env wiring lives in
# `activate.sh`. This file now thinly delegates to it so direnv users
# and `source ./activate.sh` users get identical exports. fish users
# source `./activate.fish` (hand-mirrored sibling).
#
# Why not `source_env activate.sh` (the direnv-native form)?
# `source_env` runs in a direnv-restricted shell that strips most of
# the dynamism `activate.sh` relies on (zsh/bash detection,
# dotenv_if_exists, conditional execution). A plain `source` runs the
# script in direnv's actual bash subshell, picking up every export the
# way an interactive shell would.
#
# Side effect: editing `activate.sh` triggers direnv re-evaluation
# automatically (direnv tracks file mtimes referenced inside `.envrc`).

# shellcheck disable=SC1091
source "$PWD/activate.sh"
